The incident on Friday has thrust security back into the limelight three months before elections in France, with authorities saying it was a "terrorist" assault.The attacker lunged at four patrolling soldiers while shouting "Allahu Akbar [God is great]", a Paris prosecutor told a press conference.One of the troops was struck on the head. Another opened fire and hit the attacker in the stomach. His condition is said to be stable. He is thought to be 29, living in the United Arab Emirates. He is believed to have entered France from Dubai.